<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="20" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1436,1090,1276]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,272,1090,1116]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[279,343,1091,1116]" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Syllis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[279,343,1091,1116]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Syllis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is one of the taxonomically most difficult genera within the 
<taxonomicName box="[1046,1142,1090,1116]" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Annelida" rank="family">Syllidae</taxonomicName>
due to the high diversity, lack of detailed descriptions and confusion in the generic nomenclature (
<bibRefCitation author="San" box="[1021,1235,1130,1156]" lastPageId="19" lastPageNumber="48" pageId="19" pageNumber="47" refString="San Martin. G. (1992) Syllis Savigny in Lamarck, 1818 (Polychaeta: Syllidae: Syllinae) from Cuba, the Gulf of Mexico, Florida and North Carolina, with a revision of several species described by Verrill. Bulletin of Marine Science, 51 (2), 167 - 196." type="journal article" year="1992">
San Martín, 
<number box="[1172,1235,1130,1156]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" value="1992.0">1992</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). The genus currently comprises more than 
<number box="[482,526,1170,1196]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" value="130.0">130</number>
species and is not homogeneous (
<bibRefCitation author="San" box="[930,1143,1170,1196]" pageId="19" pageNumber="48" refString="San Martin, G. (2003) Annelida, Polychaeta II: Syllidae. In: Ramos, M. A. et al. (Eds.), Fauna Iberica, vol. 21. 554 pp. Museo Nacional de Ciencias Naturales. CSIC. Madrid." type="book" year="2003">
San Martín, 
<number box="[1080,1143,1170,1196]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" value="2003.0">2003</number>
</bibRefCitation>
), so further revisions are necessary. Following other authors (
<bibRefCitation author="San" box="[576,784,1210,1236]" pageId="19" pageNumber="47" refString="San Martin, G. (1984) Estudio biogeografico, faunistico y sistematico de los Poliquetos de la familia Silidos (Syllidae: Polychaeta) en Baleares. Ediciones de la Universidad Complutense de Madrid 187, 529 pp." type="book" year="1984">San Martín, 1984</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Martin" box="[797,858,1210,1236]" lastPageId="19" lastPageNumber="48" pageId="19" pageNumber="47" refString="San Martin. G. (1992) Syllis Savigny in Lamarck, 1818 (Polychaeta: Syllidae: Syllinae) from Cuba, the Gulf of Mexico, Florida and North Carolina, with a revision of several species described by Verrill. Bulletin of Marine Science, 51 (2), 167 - 196." type="journal article" year="1992">1992</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Martin" box="[871,933,1210,1236]" pageId="19" pageNumber="48" refString="San Martin, G. (2003) Annelida, Polychaeta II: Syllidae. In: Ramos, M. A. et al. (Eds.), Fauna Iberica, vol. 21. 554 pp. Museo Nacional de Ciencias Naturales. CSIC. Madrid." type="book" year="2003">
<number box="[871,933,1210,1236]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" value="2003.0">2003</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Licher" box="[945,1098,1210,1236]" pageId="19" pageNumber="47" refString="Licher, F. (1999) Revision der Gattung Typosyllis Langerhans, 1879 (Polychaeta: Syllidae). Morphologie, Taxonomie und Phylogenie. Abhandlungen der Senckenbergischen Naturforschenden Gesellschaft, 551, 1 - 336." type="journal article" year="1999">
Licher, 
<number box="[1035,1098,1210,1236]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" value="1999.0">1999</number>
</bibRefCitation>
), subgenera are not accepted herein and 
<taxonomicName box="[281,398,1251,1276]" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Typosyllis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[281,398,1251,1276]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Typosyllis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is considered a synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="San Martin, 2003" authorityName="San Martin" authorityYear="2003" box="[733,1031,1250,1276]" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Syllis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[733,796,1251,1276]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Syllis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="San" box="[812,1023,1250,1276]" pageId="19" pageNumber="48" refString="San Martin, G. (2003) Annelida, Polychaeta II: Syllidae. In: Ramos, M. A. et al. (Eds.), Fauna Iberica, vol. 21. 554 pp. Museo Nacional de Ciencias Naturales. CSIC. Madrid." type="book" year="2003">
San Martín, 
<number box="[959,1023,1250,1276]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" value="2003.0">2003</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
